# Non-coder friendly guardrails

- Explain what changed and why in plain English before large code dumps.
- Prefer small steps: aim for a few files per change when possible.
- Ask when requirements are ambiguous; offer 2–3 options with tradeoffs.
- Write complete, runnable code; use clear names; add short comments only where logic is non-obvious.
- Never delete files or deploy without explicit approval.
- Never commit secrets; use environment variables and `.env.local` (gitignored).
- Propose a short plan (steps + files + how to test) before big refactors.
